  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/philosophy/domains/western/domains/continental/domains/french-theory/terms/libidinal-investment/> ;
  schema:name "Libidinal Investment" ;
  schema:description "Libidinal investment (Besetzung in Freud, often translated as cathexis) is the attachment of psychic energy or desire to an object, idea, person, or social structure. In psychoanalysis, the concept explains why people are bound to things that may not serve their interests — the attachment is not rational but driven by desire." ;
